cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of crowdsourcing and Best-Worst Scaling for obtaining sentiment association scores also involves aspects of human computation (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the consistency of the obtained results, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with sentiment analysis in different languages, which could fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) or computer vision (cs.CY) if the analysis involves visual data.
